{{Infobox journal | title = German Law Journal | cover = | editor = Russell A. Miller | discipline = [[Law]] | abbreviation = Ger. Law J. | publisher = German Law Journal GbR | country = Germany | frequency = bi-monthly | history = 2000-present | openaccess = | license = | impact = | impact-year = | website = | link1 = http://www.germanlawjournal.com | link1-name = Online Access | link2 = http://www.germanlawjournal.com/index.php?pageID=2 | link2-name = Online Archive | atom = | JSTOR = | OCLC = 47932864 | LCCN = | CODEN = | ISSN = 2071-8322 | eISSN = }} The '''''German Law Journal''''' is a [[peer review|peer-reviewed]], online-only [[open access]] [[law journal]] reporting on the developments in [[Law of Germany|German]], [[European Union Law|European]] and [[International law|international]] [[jurisprudence]].<ref name=about>{{cite web |url=http://germanlawjournal.com/about_glj.php |title=About the journal |format= |work=German Law Journal |accessdate=2011-10-21 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090513083326/http://www.germanlawjournal.com/about_glj.php |archivedate=2009-05-13 |df= }}</ref> It is published by [[Washington & Lee University School of Law]].
Publication of the journal started in 2000. The journal was co-founded by its [[editor-in-chief]], Russell A. Miller and [[Peer Zumbansen|Peer C. Zumbansen]]. The journal is published bi-monthly.
On the occasion of its 10th anniversary, the journal was honoured by the [[Federal Ministry of Justice (Germany)|German Minister of Justice]], [[Brigitte Zypries]], for being an "ambassador of German law".<ref name=press>{{cite web|url=http://www.bmj.de/enid/98579d0c6d61f0f5d123e608c224f824,29d47a706d635f6964092d0936303637093a0979656172092d0932303039093a096d6f6e7468092d093037093a095f7472636964092d0936303637/Pressestelle/Pressemitteilungen_58.html |title=BMJ &#124; Pressemitteilungen &#124; Zypries ehrt "Botschafter für das deutsche Recht" |language=German |work= |accessdate=2010-11-08 }}{{dead link|date=January 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>
